The '''Tainan Municipal Cultural Center''' ('''TMCC'''; {{zh|c=臺南文化中心|p=Táinán Wénhuà Zhōngxīn}}) is a [[cultural center]] in [[East District, Tainan|East District]], [[Tainan]], [[Taiwan]].

==History==
The construction of the center started in June 1980 and was inaugurated on 6 October 1984 as '''Tainan Municipal Cultural Center'''. In 2000, it was renamed to '''Tainan Municipal Arts Center'''. However, on 20 May 2004 it was renamed back again to '''Tainan Municipal Cultural Center'''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tmcc.gov.tw/en/index.aspx |title=About Us - Tainan Municipal Cultural Center |publisher=Tmcc.gov.tw |date= |accessdate=2014-04-30}}</ref>

==Buildings==
* Cultural Artifacts Exhibition Hall
* International Conference Hall
* Performing Hall

==Notable events==
* [[40th Golden Horse Awards]]

==Transportation==
The cultural center is accessible South from [[Tainan Station]] of [[Taiwan Railways Administration]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tmcc.gov.tw/en/Location.aspx |title=Location - Tainan Municipal Cultural Center |publisher=Tmcc.gov.tw |date=2014-03-11 |accessdate=2014-04-30}}</ref>

